<DOC><DOCNO> AP880523-0073 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-23-88 0835EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i PM-China-Floods     05-23 0304</FIRST><SECOND>PM-China-Floods,0313</SECOND><HEAD>Floods Kill 78, Injured 200</HEAD><BYLINE>By JIM ABRAMS</BYLINE><BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE><DATELINE>FUZHOU, China (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The number of people killed in widespreadflooding in east China's rain-drenched Fujian province has climbedto 78, a government official said today.   Chen Zengpo, director of the Fuzhou Economic Commission,reported the increased death toll and said he and other officialswere monitoring the level of the swollen Minjiang River followingheavy rains Friday and Saturday.   He said the Minjiang had flooded near Fuzhou, the provincialcapital, but Mayor Hong Yongshi said no deaths had been reported inthat area.   The most serious flooding was in Fujian province's northerncounties of Jianyang, Chongan and Zhenghe, where the deathsoccurred. More than 200 people were injured and more than 3,100were forced to flee their homes, according to official mediareports today.   Officials reported Sunday that 60 people had been killed in theflooding.   The nationally televised evening news showed residents wadingthrough waist-high water carrying household goods over their heads,or poling through the streets on rafts of logs lashed together.   The English language China Daily said 19,760 acres were flooded,900 homes were damaged, 400 sections of road were destroyed and 400bridges were swept away.   It said 12 inches of rain fell on one town in a 20-hour period,and that the water level of a major tributary of the Minjiang was90 feet above normal.   Fujian Vice Gov. Yu Dexin said Sunday that land transportationto north Fujian was cut off and that Gov. Wang Zhaoguo had flown tothe area to supervise rescue operations.   Unusual weather has plagued much of China this month. Hailstormskilled at least 24 people and injured more than 250 in coastal andcentral China, and a tornado in Guangdong province in southeastChina killed five people.</TEXT></DOC>